  "title": "Childcare Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>We are currently seeking a passionate and dedicated\nEnglish Childcare Teacher to join our team. The ideal candidate will have early\nchildhood certifications and a genuine enthusiasm for teaching young children.\nThis role offers an exciting opportunity to make a meaningful impact on the\nlives of our students and contribute to their educational journey in a\nsupportive and collaborative environment.</strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Plan and implement engaging and developmentally appropriate English language\nlessons and activities for preschool children.</strong></li><li><strong>Create a supportive and nurturing classroom environment that encourages\nexploration, curiosity, and creativity.</strong></li><li><strong>Foster positive relationships with children, parents, and colleagues through\neffective communication and collaboration.</strong></li><li><strong>Assess and monitor children's progress and development, and provide feedback to\nparents as needed.</strong></li><li><strong>Ensure the safety and well-being of all children in accordance with established\nhealth and safety guidelines.</strong></li><li><strong>Participate in professional development opportunities and stay updated on best\npractices in early childhood education.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Early childhood certifications (e.g., Diploma/Bachelor in Early Childhood Care\nand Education, Certificate in Early Childhood Education).</strong></li><li><strong>Passion for working with young children and a strong commitment to their holistic\ndevelopment.</strong></li><li><strong>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</strong></li><li><strong>Ability to work collaboratively in a team-oriented environment.</strong></li><li><strong>Patience, empathy, and a nurturing disposition.</strong></li><li><strong>Knowledge of child development theories and best practices in early childhood\neducation.</strong></li><li><strong>Previous experience working in a childcare setting is preferred but not required.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Competitive salary commensurate with qualifications and experience.</strong></li><li><strong>Opportunities for professional growth and development.</strong></li><li><strong>Supportive and collaborative work environment.</strong></li><li><strong>Comprehensive benefits package.</strong></li><li><strong>Opportunity to make a positive impact on the lives of young children and their\nfamilies.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>If you are passionate about early childhood education and\nare dedicated to making a difference in the lives of young learners, we invite\nyou to join our team! Please submit your resume to Macpherson@cambridge.school\nor Whatsapp to 83506156 for more details.</strong></p>",
